\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid10047969 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Can I have your full name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Elsie Bamber.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Spring Cottage, Rivington, Bolton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You're single?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 The year when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 1904.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And the place where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Bolton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Could you tell me whereabouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Right in the center, in the - amongst the mills.
 It was - it was the - what they call the freehold district. To put it - as some people do. The best people used to live in the freehold and - but it was surrounded by mills, it was right in the center of the - just a few minutes from the center of the to
wn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How long did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Until I was eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you move to another part of Bolton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, we moved up into the - more the residential part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have any brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 One sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was she older or younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Three years older than I.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well he was born in 19 - 18 - 1871. Now }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 \endash  can\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  do a bit of arithmetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 He was a Boltonian. And his father before him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 He was a doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did he have any other job before or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well he was trained - he - he did get his - M.Sc. to please his father who wanted him to go into the chemistry l
ine and - he got his M.Sc. and then he got a job - in a firm in Birmingham I believe as a - chemist - chemical analyser and - analytical chemist I should say, and then to please himself, he didn't like this job, and he always wanted to be a doctor so - he
 
told his father that he didn't want this job, which is a very good one - financially it was very good - and - so his father said, oh well, you go in for it if you want but - I wouldn't say that he said you're not going to get any help from me, but - but h
e did - he did lecture - to pay for his - training, as a doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 He lectured in chemistry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
He lectured in all kinds of things, anything - any subject, yes, he was particularly good on chemistry of course and - biology and he lectured - on the - surgery subjects as well, when he knew enough about it to be able to lecture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Who would he lecture to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 The students. Students in the university I presume. I'm not - I'm not so sure about this. He was at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 Owen\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  in Manchester. So I - I - I wouldn't say for certain that he was lecturing to the university students but he was lecturing - in these subjects.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When he started practicing as a doctor did he continue to do any lecturing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No, no, he didn't do anything else, he just simply practised.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And he practised as a doctor until he retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well she was born in 1873, so - I'm leaving you to do the arithmetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
She came from - well she was a - in Bolton, she'd come to Bolton when she was eight, from Edinburgh. Her father was a Doctor of Divinity and he was - minister in - Bolton church, Presbyterian, St Andrews ch
urch, for twenty-five years before - until he died. So she had been here - from the age of eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you know whether she had any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No, oh no, she didn't have any kind of a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, she was just a - housewife. It wasn't done in those days, you were looked down upon in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How many rooms in the house in which you were brought up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How many rooms? I should think - you mean bedrooms, well - one, two, three, four, fiv
e - five or six bedrooms and - sitting room, dining room, numerous passages and - kitchen, scullery, cellars and surgery, waiting room, consulting room and dispensary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did anybody else besides your parents and you and your sister live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, two maids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were there any other relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. Not at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have any other domestic help at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well we had a man who came in - twice a week I think to - clean the car and - attend to the coal and - things like that, windows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did the two maids divide their work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Now I wonder if I remember that. I think one of them did the - what you would call the - the hard work, you know, the scrubbing, and there was plenty of it in - in those days and also
 because there was all the surgery to do everyday. One of them did the surgeries I think and the - and the other one was - attended more to the meals and - and the ordinary household. One did the cooking - and - my mother did a lot of that though, and - a
ttending to the house and the other one - did pretty well the surgeries and - and did the heavy work of the house, you know, the scrubbing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Where did they sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well they had a - they - we had two - two connecting rooms in the attic. As well as
 one other one. My sister and I shared one, and the - two maids had the other connecting rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did the maids eat in their own quarters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, in the kitchen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Or with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was there anywhere that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608  they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  could sit when they were not working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Only in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your mother supervise the housework personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you feel at ease with the maids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Had a great time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did the members of the family each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you mean how did I address my parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, the maids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Oh the maids. Oh sir and ma'am, my father and mother, they addressed them as sir and ma'am. And - they addressed me as Miss Elsie and my sister as Miss Helen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did you address the maids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well, Ruth and Nellie, yes, whatever their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  name was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you feel that either of them was interested in you as a person?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. I'm thinking particularly - of course we - we had a - we didn't keep the same mai
ds all the time although - most of them stayed with us for - well at least five years, and one we had for seventeen years and - some of them stayed, you know, any time in between that, but - I'm sorry, what was the question?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did either of them seem interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 In - in - in us - yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 ? T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 hey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 were interested and - they - they treated us just as they would their own family really I would say, when we were children. I mean, they - they - they would talk to us - I wouldn't say that they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 talked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 to us perhaps as they would talk to each other but - they did - they were interested in what we were doing and - and - they were interested enough to talk to us and read to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your mother give any moral guidance to her servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well - I remember one - this particular girl was - a Welsh girl, she was eighteen. I thought that was frightfully old of course. But - she never darned any stockings. Now in those days of course one did darn stockings. And she used to throw them in the 
fire - as soon as they got a hole in, even though she was only getting a wage of perhaps five shillings a week, I don't know how she managed, but - she would throw them in the fire rather than darn them, she never - she would never dream of darning anythi
ng. So my father - my - I can remember my mother - laying the law down about that to her. So - oh she would - give - give them some advice if she saw that they needed it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were they allowed any time to do just what they liked, did they have free time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Oh yes, they had - they had free time, they had - let's see, Wednesday half day and Saturday or Sunday - free, in which they could of course do as they liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were they both off together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, I think they - I think usually they were - 
they were off separately. We didn't always have two maids, there was - maybe the one coming and - the other going, but - whenever there were two they didn't - they didn't have time off together. Unless they particularly wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your mother mind what they did when they had their free time, about the time they came back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh they always came back about ten, now whether she had laid - that down to them or not I don't know. I really }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  know. But I should imagine she would - or perhaps it was
 - the general thing for maids to come in at a certain time, at ten o'clock. We never seemed to have any who wanted to stay out longer anyway, they - they weren't the - the type of girls you get nowadays you know. You - can't imagine the girls of nowadays
 
doing - hours they did. And leading the life that they led. Of course - in those days - the - the windows for instance were - of that - that - what do you call it - you know, so that you can't see through them. That - obscure glass so that - they couldn't
 
see out at all. Well, in both houses that I remember living in, we had the - my father had that glass taken out and clear glass put in so that they could see out. And after all, from the kitchen in the first house that we lived in the - the only view was 
the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 yard,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 but still it was - it was far more interesting than looking at this obscure glass. It was an - an awful life for - for maids. Just prior to this. And in the second house we went into it was the same. And my father had all the - the obscure glass t
aken out and - plain glass put in. They could look out on the garden then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Can you remember any of these maids very clearly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes, one - one in particular, the one we had for seventeen years because I knew her right up to her death only very 
- well? I'm saying a short time ago, it's since we came into this house because I - I brought her into this house for her to finish her life here. Oh about - fifteen years since perhaps she passed on. So I do remember her extremely well, she was with us f
or so long. I also remember some that we had when I was much younger. Nellie came to us, this particular one I'm speaking of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 someone }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 who was with us seventeen years, she came go us when - I was a bout - eight or nine I should think. And - and stayed for sev
enteen years and then - decided that she wanted to leave and - there had been a few arguments between my mother and her and - I suppose it - she'd outstayed her - I wouldn't say she'd outstayed her welcome but - she had - she wanted a change. I don't thin
k she ever went into domestic service again though, I think she just stayed with her relatives. And then - we used to keep in touch with her of course and then - as I say, I brought her up here when she wasn't happy at home. So - I do remember her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You say the domestic servants at that time did have a pretty tough time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well, I think a lot of them did. You see, there was very little, apart from the cotton - the factories, and the - domestic service for girls in those days. It was - unheard of for them to go into any kind of profession of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you think the domestic servants had a better or a worse time than the girls in the mills?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well - you can't generalize really because - if they got good - into a good house with good master and
 mistress well - then it would be far - far better I should imagine than being in a mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 In general do you think that your maids }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  happy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Yes, they were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You say your mother did some of the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. And she organised everything. She always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did she do the menu planning and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Yes, oh yes, she would do that, yes. And then she did a lot of sewing for us and - she used to make our own - our own clothes. Although she had - we also had a - a woman came in, 
a seamstress I suppose she would be, she used to come in occasionally to make some things. But my mother made quite a lot of our clothes - not her own thought. This seamstress did hers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Who did the mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Mending - oh she did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 The maids didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 washing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Oh the - the heavy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 washing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 , the sheets and things were sent out but - all the rest was done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was that to a laundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 I think it was to a laundry. I'm a bit vague abou
t that, I don't really remember. But - oh I think the sheets and - were sent out, as soon as they were - well I don't know when the laundry started, do you know? No. No, but anyway they were - yes, no, I - no, I think it was a - I think it must have been 
a laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have new clothes pretty frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
No. No. It was - no, I think - we were - were just given new clothes when we needed them but - when we grew out of them, but we didn't have a wardrobe full of clothes. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about shoes, would they be bought in town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
In town, yes. YES? I remember - my mother was always very particular about shoes, getting the right fit you know, and - I can remember the first pair I went for on my own, I was twelve, and she wasn't well enough 
to take me so - I went on my own. I went to the - the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 shoe shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 that we always did go to and I was very - felt very proud of myself, even - even though I was twelve. Of course nowadays the children wouldn't think anything of going for a - set of clothes at that age.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were the shoes mended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Yes, we used to have them sent down to - to - the cobbler every - now and then. Yes, I remember those going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your father help at all with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh no. Except - t
he electrical jobs you know and - anything like that but - he couldn't boil an egg even. Oh no, he was never left alone. He was never left to get his own tea ready even.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did he do things like repairs or improvements to the house at all or would you have somebody in to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
I don't remember him doing - he - he was very - very handy - not what you'd call a handyman but - he - no, he tinkered with his car a lot. He was very interested in that. But - and if there was anything }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 needing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  doing in the house he would certainly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 be able}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  to do it, but I can't say that I remember him doing much in that line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would he ever do things like washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh no. Oh he'd never dream of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 There wouldn't really be a need for it would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, but even if there was a need he would never - he would never have dreamt of it, he wasn't that type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did he do anything for you children, like dressing or undressing or bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No. No, he was - he was rather - in fact I think I was ra
ther afraid of him when I was very young because - he seemed rather distant from us. Which was a pity, and I think he realized it later on in life, he realized it and was sorry for it, that he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 hadn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  spent more time with us. But when we were - very young -
 and particularly during the '14-'-8 war, he was so frightfully busy that - he could be excused for - and he wasn't really interested in children I think. He used to - I do remember the occasions when he did play with us, those stick out in my mind and - 
I'm very glad for those memories. We had a swing in the nursery and - he used to come up and - give us a swing on it you know just for a few minutes. But I don't remember ever - really having - any - talks with him or - you know, playtime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have a nanny or anybody like that at any stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes, until we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did she live in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
No. She came - she lived quite near. And - she used to come in every morning and - I think she must have come before breakfast, I wouldn't be 
sure about that, this is - I'm going back - to the days before I went to school now of course. But I do remember her - putting us to bed, which I suppose she would do every night. And she gave us our meals in the nursery sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was she responsible for your upbringing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
No, I wouldn't say that she was responsible, no. No, she used to read - books to us of course when my mother was busy. But she - that's what she was really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Where did you have your meals normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well - when we were 
very young I think - I seem to remember having them in the nursery mostly. But - on state occasions we would go down to the - dining room. And if there were visitors we very often were taken down to the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How much time was your mother able to spend with you in the nursery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Oh be quite a lot of time. You're speaking now of when I was - before I went to school aren't you? No, I - I don't know that she spent a lot of time with us - when we were old enough to be left to ourselves then we w
ere left to ourselves pretty much. My sister and I just - played on our own. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 And there was a - a young friend next door who used to come in and join us. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 The - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 neighbour's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 child was about - my sister's age. And then when my sister started going to schoo
l there were others who - came in, that she met at school you see and lived near. Well they didn't live very near, that was the trouble, the - the - I wasn't allowed to mix - as I said, I was - I was sheltered and I wasn't allowed to mix with the - other 
c
hildren in the same street. It was a - a street, very peculiar, it's still there, with large houses on the one side, that's the freehold, and on the other side are the small cottages. And I wasn't allowed to mix with these - small cottage children. I reme
m
ber once I - I - I was very fond of young children and - I must have been about four myself and I remember - bringing home - a very scruffy dirty looking little thing of about the age of two and I brought him into the garden and I was playing with him in 
the soil you know. My father came out and sent this child off, and I never - it never dawned on me why - whether he was - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 afraid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 of me getting contaminated with germs or what, or just that I wasn't allowed to mix with that class, I really don't know. So - w
e were rather - left to ourselves, my sister and I were rather left to ourselves, until we - started going to school and then we brought these other children home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When you had the nanny would you say that she or your mother was more with you and responsible for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh, my mother. Oh yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 She really supervised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your father read to you at all or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No. No, he never - he never mixed with us really at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. No, not without - no, we went out as a family you see but - no, h never took us out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did he ever look after you while your mother went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, I don't think so. No. I don't think my other ever - 
went - went - all - there was always somebody in you see, there was always someone that - staff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have any tasks to carry out in the home as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well we were taught to be - to put our things away and all that kind of thing but I - w
ouldn't say that we had any tasks. Not as such, we used to - help - occasionally with - well, when my mother was baking the bread for instance - things like that but there were no set tasks to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did the older of you help the younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You mean - I don't - don't remember my sister ever helping me. No. I think when we - when we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 too young to dress ourselves there was - this nanny who used to be there you see. Or my mother. I do remember being got up and put to bed by somebody but - we were never left - to do that for ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 It would be your mother or the nanny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were you expected to go to bed at a particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Oh yes, definitely. I remember being - having to go to bed at six. And I think it was jus
t - about the time I was starting school, I was - well I was six years old, and - I think when I was about twelve I seem to remember going at half past seven. So - it was early, yes. It was early for - well - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 today\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  standards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 About how old would you be when you started putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 I don't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 really}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  remember. No, I don't - I don't remember - that at all
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you and your sister share a bed or did you have separate beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, we had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 separate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  beds - in the same room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. I didn't mention it but there - we had one. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How often were you bathed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Twice a week - if I remember rightly. Yes, think it was twice a week. We were - bathed together in the same bath, I remember that. Y
ES? YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about changes of clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well every week. Every Saturday I think we had to change our clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Where did the family have their meals normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 In the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were there ever any occasions when you would eat in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No. Oh no. No. No, we never - in front of the fire, no. No, it wasn't done in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Where was the cooking done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was it a cooking range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, it was the old fash}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 ioned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4732608  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was there a gas cooker or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
No, no, it was the old fashioned fire - range. With a - you know, the oven on the one side and - I think there was water on the other. You know, a boiler, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 About what time would the normal breakfast be eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Eight o'clock. Always eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Who would be present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh - all of us. Yes, we'd be there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What did you normally have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 The usual - English breakfast. Porridge and - bacon and egg. Toast and marmalade and that kind of thing.
 Except during the - war when we had these things cut down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You'd have something to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was it any different arrangement on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, I think it was nine o'clock on Sunday. Instead of eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 The same sort of food though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Yes, we didn't make any difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about lunchtime, what did you call your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 We called it dinner. Yes. I think it was the usual thing in Lancashire in those days. But in any case it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What would you have at dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 Well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 we had a full course - you know, the soup and - and then meat a vegetables and pudding and - think we'd have had coffee - no, we didn't have coffee, I think we had a drink of tea. Afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would you al be there at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Oh yes. No, not at the same time because - my father was - we - we never - never knew when he was coming in you see. He was - sometimes - he always tried to be there for half past one but - or one - no, did I say one o'clock - it was half 
past one later, he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 tried}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  to get there for one' o'clock but sometimes he was - alter and even after two o'clock before he came in.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What was your next meal after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 A kind of high tea about five. And then - just a - a drink before went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would your father be there for the high tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 .

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would he be there regularly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Yes, he - he did manage that because - the surgery started at six so he - he always had to try to be there, but - but - as far as the midday meal 
was concerned, he was doing his visiting in the morning and of course he never knew when he would be get - getting back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You say your mother made her own bread, did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Or bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes, all those things. And marmalade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Pickles - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
No. We - she - we never make it. We had a wine cellar which - had a few bottles in brought out on - state occasions, and Christmas and like that. When we were having parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about medicines, did your mother or father make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you mean - mixed - herbs and - and suchlike? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you grown your own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. We on
ly had a small - garden. And being in the - centre of the - smoke, I don't suppose anything would have come up, and I don't suppose we'd have wanted to eat it if it had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 So you would buy all your fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would it always be fresh or would they ever be tinned or dried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 I don't remember any tins. There was always fresh. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did they keep any livestock for the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Livestock? No, only domestic animals. No. Only a cat and dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How many times a week did you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Every day I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Maybe - I do remember - oh no, it was - tongue I'm thinking of, that was - that was another thing my mother did. She made her own - tongues. Pressed them. No, I don't remember any tinned meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No, not a rabbit district either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  seeing your mother go short of a favourite dish so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I h
ave - I've no doubt she did, but I never - perhaps I never realized it. I never realized - if there was any - any shortage, and there was of course later on, I don't remember that - that I ever noticed that she wasn't having as much as we had. And - I don
't suppose she did go short but she might have - sacrificed something that; she liked so that we could have it, certainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Could you talk during the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Could you choose what you wanted from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well it depends upon when you're speaking of. I remember during the war - we had to have - we had to have one piece of bread before we could have jam on it. And - things like that. And then - if there was any vegetable we didn't 
like we had to have a bit of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  attitude if you attempted to leave some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh well I remember once very clearly. I'd left a piece of dry bread, and - and I was I was really rather late for school 
and I - I just got up from the table and rushed off and put my hat on and - and - my father called me back. He pointed to my plate and he said, what have you left that for? Piece of - dry crust. So I - I had to have it. I had to eat it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 If there was 
something on the table that you wanted such as the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh we'd ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Could you ask for second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 I think - oh yes. Well we did anyway, yes, we did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were you taught to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I suppose - I suppose we must have been because - I don't remember actually being taught that. But then - I'd only be about two or t
hree I suppose when I began to handle a knife and fork, so I - I really don't know, I do know that - I can remember my sister and I used to have small - you know, dessert knives and forks rather than table ones. Until - right until we were - in our teens 
I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Could you bring toys or a book to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. Well we never - never thought about it I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well we'd say, please may I leave the table, and - or my mother would say, well - you can go on and play now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you always have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Who served it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 My mother and my father, between them. It depends on - my father served the meat and my mother served the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Who would bring it in to the table, would it be the servant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 The maid, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I think my father was served first. I can't say - I can't say as I'm sure that I d
o remember that. I'm pretty well - I'm pretty sure that he would be. And then - my sister and myself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would the maid have the same food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes, they had the same food as we had. They used to wait until we'd finished and then - or sometimes - m
y mother would - ring the bell for them to come for - what was left for them you see. Or sometimes it was left in the kitchen for them, depending upon what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was your mother an easy sort of person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh I think so. You mean for us
 to talk to? Yes, she was - easy to talk to but - we never really had very much - what you'd call conversation. I think - her life was - her home and the church, and us of course, but - I can't say that we - that I remember discussing things with her. I r
emember she did - admonish - admonish us if there was anything that we'd done - you know, very dreadful. Well, I suppose she did whether we had - whether it was dreadful or not, but - I can't say that I remember discussing things with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you remember if you felt you cold confide in her if you had anything specially worrying you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I don't know that I ever had anything worrying me you see, that's the trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Yes. But she rather - resented too much - show from us. I think she - was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 afraid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  of us getting - well - over emotional perhaps. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 
But - I do remember - when I was - oh I was very young - and I just - threw my arms round her neck and - gave her a resounding kiss and she said, oh don't be silly, and - I do remember that very clearly. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And I think it hurt me at the time. And I think possibly - that was her attitude, that - don't be - don't be too - emotional.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You say your father was a bit distant, did you ever feel that you could talk to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
No. No. I couldn't really because - but then again you see there was - I hadn't any problems to talk to them about. Except once I remember I was very worried about my mother because she wasn't well, and rather than talk to him I wrote him a letter. And 
left it - left it for him in the surgery. I was still at home. But I wrote him a - this letter rather than talk to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 That's significant isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And he did talk to me afterwards, but not very much. He was a very - very - strong silent type y
ou know and - a man of few words. And people used to say that he - he didn't speak much but whatever he said was worth listening to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh respectfully but - not - I don't know that any laws 
were laid down. I think we was just - we just grew up naturally to - respect them and - do as we were told. But - what they expected - I - well I suppose if we'd done anything other than they expected we'd have heard about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were you brought up to behave towards your sister in any certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well - we did have rows. We weren't at all alike and - we were - I don't say - I wouldn't say that they interfered - when - when we were having out - set-tos but - we were told to keep quiet of course if we were making too much noise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did they ever say that you should hit back if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I think in those days - if we ever did think
 about - the future, it would be - the standard pattern for those times, for a girl - would just simply - marry and have children and settle down and be happy for the rest of her life. But - I don't think that they would ever have dreamt of - of - either 
o
f us going in for any - work of any kind. I did say - I remember at one time, that I would like to - I think it was - I would like to be a typist I think at that time, and - my mother just said, oh well, just finish your - finish your music exams before y
ou think of anything like that. I was going in for music you see but - I wasn't - anywhere near a professional standard, so that - I didn't - I didn't get the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 typing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  or anything 'til - I didn't do anything except my mother - my father's books. And - I did enjoy doing that. But then that wasn't very much. That was later of course, that was after I'd left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your parents bring you up to consider that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well - my father never really talked to us about - l
ife in general. My mother used to - well we went to church and I think she really - I think they both probably really left it to the - the church and the school to educate us, they - their idea I think would be give us a good school and - and take us to }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 church}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  and we would develop in the right way ourselves. And they would, of course, keep a restraining hand on if we - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 seemed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  to be overstepping the mark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What did they think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh I never heard any. I never knew anything about it - except - of course as I say, the - the other side of the street.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When the grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well we were allowed to - I've no doubt, but - we didn't. We were - rather subdued you see with - we - we didn't convers
e. I - I wouldn't say that we were stopped from talking because we never really started it. We just listened. I don't remember entering into much conversation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well we would be told about it and probably sent to bed. I remember being sent to bed early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was that the standard punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, I think so, I think - I think that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was there any physical punishment ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Who would it be, your mother or your father, or possibly your nanny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well - no, my mother. I think if my father had ever said anything it - I would have remembered it because I - it would have impressed me far more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 So it would be your mother you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
No, I can't say that I do. Yes, I do. Once when - but I wasn't punished, I was just given a good talking to and - my mother talked to mea and - trying to find out what was
 in my mind. I was - I remember going to school once and - and a child - in the street who - I don't know whether - if - whether he'd - I suppose he must have - said something to me that - you know, was very rude, and I started chasing him. And I chased h
i
m all the way down the street. And then - I went on to school, I - I didn't catch him. But - apparently that child had gone home and told his parents you see that I had - I don't know what he told them, but anyway - I remember my - when my mother was brus
h
ing my hair that - evening, she said - she asked - me about this incident and - that I - that I must - oh - shy - why had I slapped this child. I said, well I haven't slapped him. So evidently - this had come to my father's earn you see, very quickly, the
 same do. So I do remember that, but I can't say that I remember anything else particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did you feel about that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well - I felt - I felt furious - at the time, you know, when the - this child had been rude to me, but - I suppose afterwar
ds I must have felt sorry for - sorry for it. But I can't say as I - remember what my feelings were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What did you feel about the fact that it had been brought to your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 parent
\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  attention?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh well - oh well it was a bit of a - it was a bit of a shock they'd heard about it certainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents equally or from your mother more you're your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 From my mother in word but - my father - from my father in - e
xample I suppose more than - well, from both of them you see, example, but it would be my mother who would - who would teach us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes, it was a red letter day. Well it was to me
, yes. Well probably have a - a special tea of, you know, something that we liked and - presents of course, that's all. I don't know that we - there would be anything different otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have guests in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No, well - sometimes I had a party, a birthday party of course, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Just sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Yes, when I was going to school when - I - I do remember having parties, not every birthday but - I do remember one in particular. I had about - twenty of my school friends - to a party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Can you remember how you spent Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Yes, I do remember that because - my sister and I wouldn't sleep on Christmas Eave and then - this was before - we - this was when we believed in Father Christmas of course, and - I remember - 
on one Christmas Eve in particular - my sister and I saying oh we were - we were going to keep awake this particular night, we'd always fallen a sleep before, so - we kept prodding each other awake and - we - we were sleeping in the same bed on this occas
i
on and - my mother kept coming in and saying are you two not asleep yet? And I don't know what hour we kept them up until. My father came in once too. What are you two doing awake? We're waiting for Father Christmas. Oh well, he won't come while you're aw
a
ke, you'd better go to sleep. So - eventually I suppose we did but there was always the - the stocking at the bottom of the bed full of the usual things. Well at least usual for those days, I don't know what it is nowadays. A sixpenny piece and - nuts and
 an orange and an apple and a - a little odd toy, something like that you know. Maybe two or three toys. But - I do remember that and it was always - always the same, but it was always a thrill - to get this - stocking.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have a special Christmas Dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well, we always - had - you see we had about eighteen - no, fourteen of us for midday dinner. Yes, a turkey dinner. And then - we had other people - another lot of people in in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would these be relatives or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, relatives - relatives and friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you ever go out for Christmas Day to anybody else's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Yes, we used to go up to my grandmother's house when we were - very young. I don't know when we stopped going there, I think I was - about seven or eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Yes. We had a - a grand piano and a - an organ in the other room. And when my sister and I started learning at the age of five or six my father sold both the organ and the piano and bo
ught two uprights so that we could each practice at the same time. And get it over with. In different rooms, yes. But then we were barred from practicing in the dining room - in surgery hours because he could hear it. And we had an old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  - with a 
- I think it must have been a very old one when we were children, it was a - it had an enormous horn, about that length, and - we had a few - good many - old records. We used to - spend a lot of time with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did anybody sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 My sister learnt singing, yes. This was later of course. And I accompanied her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 Did you have musical get-togethers at all in the house?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, whenever we had friends in - in the evenings, they were - we would have a musical evening. And - most people in those da
ys were able to do something. Then we had charades or - something like that you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 
That would be at a party of course but - we didn't have - musical evenings as musical evenings regularly, it was only just when we had a lot of people in, in the evening.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, my mother used to play, things like snakes and ladders. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about outdoor games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And - well we were never out of doors because we hadn't any ground you see, we only had this - garden. Bit of garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Had a - a large book - old fashioned Victorian book - book case full of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well we used to get the daily papers, yes. Magazines, Home Chat and Home Notes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Yes, my mother used to read a lot. My father never seemed to have time. He did used to read certainly but I can't say what books he used to read - apart from the - daily papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did they ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well my mother did, yes. Sundays mostly I remember, Sunday afternoons, that was - or Sunday morning, I don't know whether it's - no, we used to go to Sunday school so - it must have been when we were very young that she w
ould read to us, before we went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you remember there ever being a funeral in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were you taken out to visit neighbours or friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, occasionally. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would it be mainly friends and relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Friends and relations, yes, I think it would probably be a - a weekly thing when we were young, before we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about neighbours, would you visit neighbours at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, we hadn't any - any connection at all
 with the neighbours. Except next door as I said where this child about our age, she used to come and play with us. We used to go there occasionally.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When you were taken to friends or relations would it be with your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well, if 
they were - very often with my mother to visit a particular friend of hers, but - my father used to take us out - maybe a Saturday or Sunday - to visit his friends. We - we'd go - we'd all go then of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
No. There was an occasion where it was arranged, he - I remember him suggesting that we cycled to Blackpool. Why he got this idea I don't know, my sister and I had just recently got cycles and I was about - twelve or thirteen and - and he was going t
o get hold of a - a cycle and - and he was going to take us to Blackpool, which I would have thoroughly enjoyed. But for some reason or other we never went. So I can't say that he ever took us out on our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you remember any other outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes, we used to go - in the car to - Skipton and Bolton Abbey and - you know, within easy distance of Bolton. And - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 Harwood}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  and round about and - visit friends at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 Wilmslow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 . Yes, we frequently went out for - a day. Or half a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I don't think Bank Holiday ever made any difference to us really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. We'd go to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 Regularly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh every year, yes. We'd go to - my father didn't always go on the - on t
he holidays. No, he would come and visit us at weekends, we would go to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 Lytham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 or Fleetwood or - Blackpool or Cleveleys, and then at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608  Easter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 we generally went to a farm at Harwood. And - we really - we really enjoyed that. He would leave us there, sometimes
 just the two of us children you see and - and then our friends from school would come up - and we'd have a great time up at the farm then. But we didn't often go away all together. My father never seemed to bother about holidays actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When you went to Blackpool or somewhere on the coast there your mother would take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well we just played on the beach. We didn't - we didn't really do much. And then we generally found friends - or - school
 - schoolmates there you see. Everybody seemed to go away to Blackpool or Fleetwood in those days and - we would meet other and - arrange to meet them and play with them you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your mother spend much of her time with you while you were on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Oh - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did you spend your Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Do you mean - schooldays or - well I always seemed to - seemed to have quite a lot of homework to do. And then - we would go out - as I say, my father would take us out 
most weekends I think, or - either Saturday or Sunday. But - I can't say that I remember any particular thing - any different on Saturdays except that we would - have more time to play in - when we got our homework done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about Sundays, you say you went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well yes, went to church in the morning, and - Sunday school in the afternoon and then - don't remember the evenings really, I suppose we would read or - have a musical evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have special clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Yes. Very special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you play games at all or did your parents think it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 On a Sunday? I don't know that we ever - we were never told that it was wrong and I can't say that I remember specially playing games. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 
I suppose we would have played games perhaps in the evening, if we - I think it was considered if we went to church in the morning and Sunday school in the afternoon that - we - the evening was more or less free. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 But - I can't say that I remember whether it was laid down that we shouldn't play games. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your parents attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, my mother did, my father didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was your mother Presbyterian?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes. My father had been - a Wesleyan an
d - in fact he taken a - he'd taken a very prominent part in the church, but - that was when he was younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your mother go regularly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Oh yes.
