ent times, caterpillars and suchlike. We went in for pen painting and - drawing and things like that. Art.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you ever go fishing or cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Cycling, yes. But not - only just - only just for a half an hour round the houses, that kind of thing.
 Or just out into the country for half a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you do much walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, not - only - only at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Tennis. And French cricket - what do you call it, netball.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you go to any theatres or concerts, music halls or cinemas or anything like that while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes, occasionally but not - not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of things would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well we used to go to - the dra
matic society and the - music - think it was - once a year they had this musical - evening. Concert. And - I don't know that there was much else in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you go to any commercial entertainments, the Grand or the Hippodrome?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, becaus
e my father - my father's friend was one of the agents for the - for the - theatres, the music halls. In fact it was he who found Gracie Fields, and - so we used to go - we used to be taken to the - the music hall programmes. Very often to different place
s to, not just Bolton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have any pocket money as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, sixpence a week. Penny a week to begin with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was that regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Every Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did you spend it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well, on sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was there any occasion 
when your mother had help to look after the house or family, any relatives, friends or neighbours in any crisis situation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, no, there wasn't any crisis really, we never had any. We had a - an aunt - an aunt of mine, my mother's sister lived with u
s for several years off on, well she helped. I can't say that - it was only just for something to do, not because it was necessary.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did she live with you when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No. That was later when her mother died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
No. Well my mother - mother's family - my mother's mother and her sister and brothers lived in Bolton but - they were more often away than - of course the brothers were away from home. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 More}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  often than not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 She kept in quite close contact with her mother didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you come into close contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Your parents did have some friends didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Where did they see them, visiting each other's houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Or on other occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, that was - pretty well all, just - visiting each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did they share the same friends or did they tend to have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 independent}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  friends of their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well each had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 independent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  friends but then - they also shared. I mean there was - there was nothing - well, yes, they each had their own friends but not - they didn't keep them entirely apart from the - the husband or wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Taking your mother and her friends, did she visit them in their homes, did they come to your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And the same with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were friends invited into the home pacifically?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Or did they tend just to drop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh they didn't drop in because it was 
a - an awkward - an awkward situation in a doctor's home, you can't just drop in to see a doctor I'm afraid, you just had to - well, ring up and see if it's all right to come. Not as people would here for instance now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 The friends who came would be offered something to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would there be particular days or occasions when you'd have friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh, first Thursday of every month. In the case of my mother it was - you know, the - old at home days that we used to have. F
irst Thursday of every month, I think I mentioned that to you before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of people would come to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I remember my - one or two of my teachers at school used to come. And her friends who were - more distant - more distant - ac
quaintances shall we say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You didn't have very close contact with the neighbours did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did they ever come into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, except the - the - one or two that we did - we were friendly with, next door people for instance. They were popping in and out, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And you likewise went into their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes, when I was a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your parents go out often to visit their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When they did get together with their friends what sort of things did they do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well in the case of my father it was bridge, that's the main interest. And - and mother it was just a - kind of social call. I don't - they didn't do anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 They would talk more than anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Occasional theatre perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Can you tell me something about the community in which you did live, you spoke about your house being in the freehold area and there being these children in houses nearby that you weren't allowed to associate with, thinking of yourself as a scho
olchild did you think of some people belonging to one social class and others to different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
I suppose - no, I - I didn't until - I was at - when I was at school and we had these - children coming with grants to the school. And - I think I mentioned that to you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 before}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
 that - that the others were rather looking down on them and I didn't see why they should. It was only - they were obviously - from a different class of - type of people, but they didn't strike me that they were any - I never thought 
of them as being - lower - lower order, until these other - you know - the - my friends - rather looked down on them and - and it was then that I began to be influenced I suppose, but it didn't influence me for long. I saw the shallowness of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How d
id you perceive the sort of structure of the adult world, did you see people in different spheres of life as belonging to different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You're speaking of when I was a child are you? Well it's difficult to say, I don't - I don't know. I don't th
ink I ever thought about it, I just took people as I found them. Until I was told not to - associate with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of people would the parents be of the children you weren't allowed to associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well they were very rough. You could hear - swearing and all that kind of thing, awful language that they used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would they come from particular occupational groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well they - they were the - what you'd call the - the lower classes, the - mill people and some in those days they re
ally were very rough some of them. I wouldn't have told them my parents were keeping me away from those children 'cos - the - the children themselves of course - had awful - awful language. They didn't know any better poor things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How far would their roughness go in their contact with each other, if there was a family }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 where they were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  really beyond the pale as it were, would other people show their disapproval in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well - well, I do - I do remember vaguely they were - there were - rows in 
the street, you see it was - I think I told you that - that - there was a - one class of house on one side of the street and - the other class, just the opposite on the other. It was rather peculiar really. Very interesting too. But - oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608 we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 used to hear rows among the next door neighbours}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3429630\charrsid4732608  who }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 would come out and join in the row and - and then they would settle it between then I suppose. I don't say that that was going on all the time but - we did have it now and again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did it just stick at verbal rows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Yes. Well the children of course were - having rows and throwing each other around but - oh no, I don't say that they got to this stage where - sort of thing that you see outside pubs, or at least that type of thing you used to see outside pubs. Oh n
o, it was - it was just - wasn't going on all the time by any means.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 These would be mainly mill worker types of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of people would belong to the same as your household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you mean - in the same road or - no -
 well there wasn't anybody in the area at all. No. There was a - a minister who was friendly with my father, he used to come but - there was nobody else that I can remember that we could - you could say that were our type - at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What about the people next door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Oh well they were - well we used to play with the - the children three you see, but - oh my father and mother used to - they were - they weren't friends but of course they used to - just as one is with our - with your next door neighbour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of job did the father have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 They were - oh - fireplace people. Managing - in a fireplace firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 So they were commercial?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 So there'd really be only your father and the minister in the professional class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes. So far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were you brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was there ever anybody that you were told to curtsey to or show respect to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh no. Oh no. We were taught our - manners, but that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was there anybody that you had to call sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did people call your parents sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did people tend to regard your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh with great respect. And - but friendly respect. He was - he
 was able to come down to - people's level. And he was able to come up. Just as necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Who would be considered the most important people then in that district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I don't know whether anybody was - anybody looked upon anybody as any more important than anyone else really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Do you know what sort of people certain categories would have associated with, for instance the clergy, who would they tend to associate with on a social level?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I didn't really - have much to do with the cl
ergy because - well I went to church regularly and - the minister used to come and visit her but - I can't say that I was mixed up with it very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 The teachers, did they associate with other teachers or more widely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You're speaking generally, not - not my - well I think they associated with each other very much. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 But - I don't remember hearing of any - general get-togethers, if that's what you mean, only in the school itself.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 There wouldn't be any farmers would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were there a-y employers that you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well only these people next door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of people would be their friends? Do you know?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, I can't say really. No, the - the husband - the husband died - very early on in my life, so I - I really don'
t know. And the son was away from home. He carried on the business you see so I really don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
What sort of people would you say went to the church, to the different sorts of churches, differentiating between Church of England and non-conformist and chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well I had friends - my friends went to - different ones. And - I don't know that they were any different from - from anybody else really. There wasn't - you can't say that there was any hard and fast rule between - one class - one - denom
ination or another. The same type of people went - went to each you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would there be a similar constitution of a congregation in each church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes, I think so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Going back to the working class people in the street, would you say th
at they all had the same standard of living or would there be different levels within the group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
I would say that they were - that - there was - well shall we say mill workers were all - almost all the same. Do you mean - their social life or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 And their standards of eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Well - so far as I could remember and - and know, I should say that they were all more or less alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you think that any group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 I don't know, you see, it - didn't enter my head that anyone could be more superior than another, so - I really don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you remember a distinction being felt between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh well - yes, the - there's a distinction there of ability. But not of status necessa
rily, not - not necessarily of - of one being superior to the other, it was just that one was not - as able - to do that particular kind of job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. I think my father perhaps was a better mixer than my mother. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 
She would rather - I wouldn't say aloof but she - she wouldn't be comfortable with - people of the lower classes as he would be. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
He would mix in with them. But - I don't suppose she would be able to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you think she saw herself as belonging to a particular social class or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Possibly. Yes, because she had been - she had been brought up in Bolton certainly, but - I think that - that the - that her life had been - more apart from the lower classes
 than my father's had you know. So that she wouldn't - she would have a - a different idea of distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would you say that it was possible in those days for people to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 I don't know, I think it would perhaps have
 been more difficult for them then than it is now. 'Cos the - for one thing they wouldn't have the same - they wouldn't have the same - chances as people have now. Of getting out of their - either educational sphere or - or their work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You don't remember anybody who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, I can't say that I can remember anyone who did rise up from the ranks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you remember anybody being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I've no doubt I did but - I can't think of anyone particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Oh yes.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What did you think about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I didn't know him personally, he was just - one of those people who had to be there. It was his - he had his job to do th
e same as anyone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I never saw any of the - any - I - I don't think I ever saw any police - in action.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your mother ever say that she'd call a policeman if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No. Thank goodness. I think that's the most ridiculous thing isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Your home would be your own property?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you remember at any stage ever feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well my father was always tal
king about - we were going to land in the work house, that was his way of putting it, but - no, I don't think so. There was no - there was no need for it certainly but my father had rather a negative attitude in that way. You couldn't afford this and you 
c
ouldn't afford that, and he would go and spend - three times the - the amount on - on something that we would have thought that he couldn't afford. It was - realize that - that when people begin to think that they're poor and they can't afford then they e
ventually come to the stage where they really can't, they think themselves into it. Sometimes see it's the power of thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You mentioned something about your father having a patient who owed something like a hundred and odd pounds and was paying it o
ff at sixpence a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Well that's an example. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 Yes, yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was that a very rare exception?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh no. Oh no, it was quite common. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of community really did he serve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well - they were mainly poor, yes. Yes, they were 
- living in that area you see. He was the doctor for - well quite a big area of Bolton and - but it was mostly the poorer end. He didn't go very much - he had a few - wealthy patients, but very few compared with the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did they in the main manage to pay for their treatment properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Oh - I would say that - I would say that half of them would. I mean they would pay - they would pay sufficient to pay it off. Unless they were chronic invalids and then of course the - it would go on and on and -
 accumulate - debts would be accumulating but - my father would never say anything to them and - of course the collector would have that job to do. And if he got sixpence a year, well - I suppose my father just realized that he couldn't get any more. That
 
they couldn't give any more. Of course it was a very different state of affairs in those days. From now, when people are earning - twenty and thirty pounds a week. I don't suppose they would - well, if the husband wasn't working I don't suppose there woul
d
 be anything - coming in at all. That was before the time of the - oh there may have been - I don't know when the employment - unemployment benefit started. Do you know? Was it, yes, I had an idea it was. I'm speaking of the times - no, not I', not speaki
ng at the time just before that - it - it went after the - unemployment benefit came in but - as far as I know my father would never say anything about it. And he would go on attending the patients whether they paid or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were you given lessons at all before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I was taught my A.B.C. and things like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was that by your mother or a nanny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I think it was both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When you first started what were the school times, what time did you go in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Oh just the same as - well as far as I remember I went in the morning and the afternoon but - there would be - up to four - or was it to half past three, I think it was up to half past three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What kind of a school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 The - Bolton school, the High School for Girls it was called then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 This would be the preparatory department would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well there was a kindergarten, yes, was a kindergarten up to the age of eight, and then - you got into the big school and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 So it was an independent school and a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was the kindergarten mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, the kindergarten was mixed and there was - when you got to - the age of eight I think it was you were sepa
rated into the - boys and girls schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Half an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did anybody go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well my sister was going to school, she used - nearly three years older than I. We went in a - body. Collected people on the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you go home for your midday meal then or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh - I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I looked - I did look upon them as superiors of course and - I liked them, I - I think I liked them all - in different ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as being important, things like manners or tidiness, punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No I don't think so, I don't think we had 
any - I think it was understood that we had to be there - had to be at school at nine o'clock and - had to come clean and - I - I remember having our - nails looked at for some reason and another but - I don't remember any - any tuition in - cleanliness. 
I don't think it was necessary really you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Not in that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did the teachers concern themselves about the way people spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No, I don't remember them saying anything about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh were sent to see Miss Diamond, the head.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were there any punishments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. Not as - no - didn't remember - any punishments really, we might have to - oh yes, I think we had to stay in for - after school, had
 to stay in another ten minutes or something and - given something to do. Perhaps go over the - homework that we - or the - the schoolwork rather that we should have done better at. I don't know. I don't know what - why we were punished. If we were - it w
ould only be because of inattention or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 It would be in the form of being kept in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would you be admonished perhaps sometimes for other things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Only by the head. Yes. I - I remember going once but I don't even r
emember what it was for. I don't say as I was a model child but - it was very rarely that anybody was - punished in the way you mean now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Physical punishment you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well no - no physical punishment. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What form did that take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well my mother would - would always attend the - end of term - exhibition of work. And - or end of year. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 And - and she would go and see the - head occasionally about - how we were going on.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did they ask you what you'd been doing at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did they look at your work, your homework and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I don't think - I don't know, I think that was entirely - left entirely to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You've already mentione
d about some of the children going to the school on grants, some of them then would come from rather different types of homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What proportion of the children would you say did come from different homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were from different homes? Oh 
a very small percentage. I think - I think we got ten - one year with whom - you know, just - oh no, it wouldn't be as many as ten, because they would come into the - same form wouldn't they. No, we would - we got two in our form and - and I think there w
ere - there may be ten altogether, over a - over a period. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 I remember two coming, then there were - one or two in the - form above, but - very, very few. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 That was just the beginning of it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
The only one I can remember - is the - the singing master, who singled out - a friend of mine who was - well she became a - a very good singer, and he singled her out to teach us really. How it should be done. But not from
 any sense of favouritism or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. No, I do-'t think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did any of the children seem to be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I'm afraid these children were that we're speaking o
f, we - we were very horrid to them I think, 'cos - we did leave them alone. To begin with. But - if they held their own, well they got in with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How old were you when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 I thin
k I was fourteen - because of illness of one kind and another and - my father thought that I wasn't learning anything in any case, he thought it was a waste of time paying my fees. He wished he'd sent me to a council school and that kind of thing. But he 
w
as probably quite right, that I didn't - I didn't learn - I - was not particularly interested in most subject and - I suppose if I'd been taught - the importance of it, of taking all the advantage that I had, I might have done better. As it was - but I - 
I was always being ill and - having colds you know and having to stay and home and - and then I had - well I don't think I had any real illnesses, just continual cold after cold and they decided that I'd better stay at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Yes. I think it was mostly because I - because my friends were still there, it wasn't because I wanted to learn anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, only in music. Not - not general education, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Oh yes, I do wish that I'd - I'd learnt more and - gone on things that I wasn't - I wasn't at all interested in, I do wish that I had - been forced to do that, to - to be - 
not - well, of course, if you - if you do study a thing you do get interested in it very often and I suppose I would have done the same thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Oh yes, I - I do think - everybody should be allowed not to go to school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What happened when you left school, did you stay at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Yes? I stayed at home. I - I did my father's books and I - I started - going to a clinic for - children. Babies. I think I went two or three days a wee
k. And - I was studying music. And painting. I had - we had a - painting teacher came and - taught us privately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Were your days at the clinic a voluntary thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have a job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. Not - not to begin with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When did you first take a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Take up chiropody? Well I was - I was thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Looking back - would you have preferred to have taken a job or gone in for a career when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. I - I would have liked to but I didn't know w
hat. Except secretarial work and of course - - my mother was keen on me - carrying on with the music and - I don't know whether she thought I wasn't - I wasn't - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507686\charrsid4732608 type}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608  for secretarial work, I don't know. But - she was quite happy for me to - take up a job later. But by that time I thought it was necessary you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You were old enough to make your own mind up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes, but I thought it was necessary from the financial point of view.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You went into chiropody, was this an obvious choice for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Oh no, it wasn't obvious at all. No, no before that I had the idea - that - I would be depriving somebody else of a job if I went into one. And - and it was only when I thought that - it was necessary from the financial point of view that I felt that
 it - that it was permissible for me to do it, you see, so - then I - went to the library and went through a - a book on careers for women and - I picked this out as - as being - interesting for me. So I went in for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 After you left school and were 
at home you did your father's books and you had your music and painting lessons, how did you spend the rest of your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh I had housework. It was all kept surgically clean. I used to rebel but - I did it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you spend your leisure time similarly to the way you had done earlier or did you start doing different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Well I read more but it was - trashy novels, I didn't - I didn't try to improve my mind for instance. It didn't occur to me to read for education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you go on going to Sunday school and church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Not in the slightest, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you exercise your vote at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes? But I - just according to - my father's views really. I didn't really know much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Apart from reading, you had been doing things like going to the theatre and so on hadn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes? not too very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you go out in the evening much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I used to go to the cinema. But - and visiting friends and bridge parties and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When you went to the cinema who would you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 A friend who lived near, well fairly near, about half an hour away. My - greatest friend who was then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you make any new friends about that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
No, because I never really met many people. It was a rather lonely bleak time - after I'd left school. Because all my friends were still at school you see. Oh I joined the tennis club and - that was - or at least I - when I was eighteen
 I joined the tennis club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You had this one special friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have any other special friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No. Not special friends, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You would take them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your parents expect to know where you were when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 I don't know that they expected it but - we - they - they knew. I never - kept anything from them, there was no - no need to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did you have to be back home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I was - we would always say if we were going to be later. And - we would be expected to be in by ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was your sister's whole school career similar to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well she got engaged - very early on and - so it was slightly different, sh
e spent her time - making things for her bottom drawer as the saying was then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did she have a job at all or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 She went in for secretarial. Yes, she - she did a secretarial training, yes. And book keeping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did she ever have a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, she never had a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of man did she marry, what sort of job did he have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well he was a traveler, commercial traveler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was he that always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did your nanny ever take you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Ever to her own home for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You said she lived near didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes? She did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of relationship were you on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I don't think she had any family, as - if I remember rightly, she just had a sister. And - I think this 
sister died so she was left on her own. I only remembered going to the house once actually. Oh yes, she didn't take us regularly. She would take us - she would take us out of course in the park and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 What sort of hours did she work, I think you told me that she came before breakfast and she was there to put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Oh well - she would - she lived near you see so she would just go home during the daytime. I can't say that I remember, she was just there or she wasn't there, it didn't matte
r to me which. No, it didn't really - it didn't really impress itself on my mind that she was there any particular time. But she would be called in if necessary you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did she come in at the weekend as well as during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I really ca
n't tell you whether it was - I don't think there was anything - definite about it, I think it was just - it would just be arranged for her to come at a certain time next day or - two or three days later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Did she have any meals with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes? She used to have meals with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Would she eat in the nursery with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Yes. Yes. That was when I was - before I went to school of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 You did have some meals in the nursery, who served you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well Letty did really, this nanny was dishing up, that's what I called her. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Was the food brought up by the maids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 No, she would bring it you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When you were very small would it be the same sort of meal that the grown up family was having?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How did your parents expect you to behave towards your nanny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well I don't think it ever - cropped up, we would - we would just - behave as we would to anyone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 How do you think she expected you to behave towards her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Well just the same I think. Just the same as we would anyone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 Do you think she had any influence on your behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 
Probably she had, she was - she was a very nice woman and - I suppose really she - just fitted in with the family and - and taught us according to how she knew that - my parents wanted us to be taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10047969 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 When you went on holiday did she ever come with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13725874 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3297407\charrsid4732608 I don't remember her ever coming, no.
\par }}